name: RNA extract
def: an extract which is the output of an extraction process in which RNA molecules are isolated from a specimen.

name: nucleic acid extract
def: An extract that is the output of an extraction process in which nucleic acid molecules are isolated from a specimen.

name: DNA extract
def: The output of an extraction process in which DNA molecules are purified in order to exclude DNA from organellas.

name: sequence alignment
def: A data transformation in which one or more sequences (reads) are positioned on a reference sequence template (often a reference set of genes), according to the genetic base-pairing paradigm.

name: sequencing assay
def: An assay the uses chemical or biochemical means to infer the sequence of a biomaterial
